# EVVIE Tests
You can run the following tests below to test the viability of EVVIE's Azure Function deployment:

## Check that the Azure Function is on: `/version`
```
GET https://timh-evvie.azurewebsites.net/version
```

## Read Plate Endpoint
This tests the `/plate` endpoint's ability to read a license plate. The image below is [this image](https://i.imgur.com/T07SV2y.jpeg). The correct plate number is **1471251**.

```
POST https://timh-evvie.azurewebsites.net/plate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "image": "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
}
```

## Inspect Endpoint
The below POST checks the viability of the `/inspect` endpoint, providing [these two images](https://imgur.com/a/mlfBflD) of front bumper damage in base64 format.

```
POST https://timh-evvie.azurewebsites.net/inspect
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "images":
    [
        "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
        "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
    ]
}
```

The correct response to the above POST is something like the following:

```
200 OK
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "area": 5,
    "description": "Significant dents and scratches with a partially detached bumper on the front right side.",
    "severityLevel": 3
}
```
